<span class="openapi-clients-box"><span class="openapi-clients-box-heading">Clients</span><a href="https://docs.apify.com/api/client/python/reference/class/WebhookCollectionClientAsync#list" target="_blank"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apify/openapi/b1206ac2adf8f39b05e5a09bf32c2802af58d851/assets/python.svg" class="openapi-clients-box-icon" alt="Apify API Python Client Reference"/></a><a href="https://docs.apify.com/api/client/js/reference/class/WebhookCollectionClient#list" target="_blank"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apify/openapi/b1206ac2adf8f39b05e5a09bf32c2802af58d851/assets/javascript.svg" class="openapi-clients-box-icon" alt="Apify API JavaScript Client Reference" /></a></span><span id="/reference/webhooks/webhook-collection/get-list-of-webhooks"></span><span id="/reference/webhooks/get-list-of-webhooks"></span>Gets the list of webhooks that the user created.


The endpoint supports pagination using the `limit` and `offset` parameters
and it will not return more than 1000 records.

By default, the records are sorted by the `createdAt` field in ascending
order. To sort the records in descending order, use the `desc=1`

parameter.
